  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The most straightforward and hacky way would be to use the helper, listen to the result event, check if there is only one value returned and hide the container of your menu:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst search = instantsearch(/* config */);\r\n// ...\r\nsearch.start();\r\nsearch.helper.on('result', (results) => {\r\n  const values = results.getFacetValues('yourMenuFacet');\r\n  if(values.length <= 1) hide();\r\n  else show();\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nhttps://community.algolia.com/algoliasearch-helper-js/reference.html#SearchResults#getFacetValues",
    "created_at": "2018-08-23T19:15:54Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/3031#issuecomment-415537665",
    "id": 415537665,
    "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/algolia/instantsearch/issues/3031",
    "node_id": "MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQxNTUzNzY2NQ==",
    "performed_via_github_app": null,
    "pin": null,
